text: <@U2H3TT8F2>, if you have a proper canonical set, does a duplicate title matter on page "duplicates"
specifically a multilang site and the query `?hsLang=lang`

I dont believe it should matter. The canonical is telling the search engines that the page in question they should look at should be "X". Then again with multilanguage sites, im not sure how Google handles that (especially with the different searches for language-specific countries). <@UHM5BT6G5> may have some insight into this though.
dont let anyone tell you otherwise
